MOTOR RACING - HILL SPINS OUT OF ITALIAN GRAND PRIX . Briton Damon Hill , driving a Williams - Renault , hit a tyre wall and spun out of Sunday ' s Italian Grand Prix on lap six . Hill , who was leading at the time , had started the race with a 13 - point lead over team mate Jacques Villeneuve of Canada and had hoped to clinch his first drivers ' championship title with a victory at Monza . 
